Partly cloudy- windy- no white caps
Algae bloom- some white like soap suds (1/4 to 5/8" in size) - sunny- calm
Partly sunny- calm- algae bloom- rocks have dark green spots on them-- some raised greenish yellow- jelly like growths
Small amount of algae- clear- calm
Clear skies- windy.  Note: up here a little late this year- weather did not permit a reading earlier in the last two weeks.
Calm- partly cloudy- slight algae bloom.  Last reading of the summer.
No clouds- pin-points of algae in water
Sunny day- a little algae bloom- more algae close to shore
Hazy sun- very calm lake- slight pinpoints of algae.
Partly cloudy-calm- sudsy near shore- very wavy yesterday.
Clear and cool- water appeared clear
No ice- clear to partly cloudy.
Some suspended particles in the water- sky is clear and sunny.

Clear- calm- cool.  Very windy previous 2 days.  Large group of Canadian Geese flying north.
Cloudy day- calm.  Saw great blue heron.  Been rainy.
Cloudy day but calm.  Loons - six babies- 4 adults (great!).
Partly cloudy- calm.  Loons young learning to fly.  Gulls arrived late July.
Clear- cold- 38 F.  Trumpeter swans back: 2 adults- 4 goslings.  Gulls still here.
Calm- a light wind- cold- 39 F.  Clear.  Loons arrived 4/13/2004.
Calm- sunny- very cool for late June + July.  6 loons.  Some immature.
Calm- sunny.  Warmer.  Lots of lillies and weeds.  Saw 6 loons yesterday.
Calm- sunny- still very cool summer.  More weeds.  2 blue herons.
Calm- sunny- warm now.  10 trumpeter swans: 8 immature- 2 adults - band #575.  Weeds!!
Light wind- cool lake is high- had lots -f wind in May- 2 pair of trumpeter swans- loons arrived 4-15-2006
calm- warm- lake is low- not much wild life
Light wind- 5 loons- one single  sea gulls too- H2O is very murky- looks like a bloom
DEEP HOLE - 6FT INTEGRATED SAMPLE     trumpeter swan male- P76- shot and killed in stumpy bay- mate- female- x88. We watched them for 9 years
X88 returned (unmated) 04-21-2007. Ice out 4-26-2007. Calm- warm and humid. Pollen. Swan P-76 mate shot
Calm. Rain on 4th. Cool a.m.- Light NW wind. Not much wildlife- heard loon.
Very Calm. Lots of weeds. Lake is extremely low due to drought.
Calm. Weeds. Lake low. Trumpeter family of 7.
Light wind- sunny cool. Air temperature 38 F. Lake is up. No pollen yet. Loons here - 4/20/08.
Windy- cool. Air temperature 60 F. So far summer is very cool.

Calm- sunny- cool. Air temperature 35 F. Lake is down. Saw 7 trumpeter swans - 2 adults and 5 goslings flying from Stumpy Bay east. Hunters must have frightened them. Lake seems very cloudy. Some residences have used herbicides- this could be the reason for cloudiness.
calm- warm - Been a very cool spring loons nested but failed.  a lot of pollen- lots of weeds on west side of lake.
light wind- cool.  Lake is very low- NFS drained hay meadow this year and no good flowage into seven mile.

calm - finally warm weather- lake still very very low.  We were told by NFS the hay meadow flowage will not be filled until reparis to the dam in late duly.  This is very stressful on wildlife- especially the loons.  Saw two pair and one lone loon.  Losing their (loon's) color and no territorial fights.  Must take boats out now because lake is so low.
Cloudy and calm. Cool. Lake is very low- but got some good rain and maybe water level will rise. Satellite is over today. Loon is alone- hopefully mate in incubating egg.
calm- cool. Lake is up. Foggy. Lake clarity is bad.
very cold spring- ice out 04/29/2011- two pairs of loons - one pair of trump swans
cool mornings - hot PM- Loons had two chicks on about 6-30-11 - hope they make it over th 4th
after a week of 90 degrees- it is a cool morning. Loons are ok - about 5 weeks old
pretty day- calm- cool- 45 degrees. 45 degrees. Loon family is doing fine. Had a cold stormy Labor Day
Cloudy- 44 degrees. Canada geese- sandhill cranes- 1 loon pair (red) - Hay Meadow pair.
Lots of algae. Lake very- very low. Lowest lake level in 13 years. Geese- loons are losing their mating colors.
Finally beautiful - 51 degrees. Clear and calm. Ice out May 10 - late spring. Didn't get the boat in the water until after Memorial Day. Then lots of rain.
assume noon. Partly cloudy. Has been cool for about 10 days. Pair of loons in Stumpy Bay. 48 degrees at night. 65 degrees for the high. Lake level is up.
July has been very cool with isolated storms. Did not see very much wildlife. Hi in the 70's. Low in the 40's.
